Sony has launched a new limited-edition PlayStation 4 Pro to celebrate 500 Million PlayStation systems sold worldwide. The console features a translucent dark blue shell, and matching DualShock 4 controller, PlayStation Camera, and mono headset. The new PS4 Pro also packs a 2TB hard drive. Sony said the console will sell for $499.99, and will be limited to 50,000 units worldwide. It goes on sale from 24 August 2018. “In addition, each system will have a commemorative copper plate on its front, with its limited edition serial number etched on,” said Sony. The limited-edition DualShock 4 will also be available separately for $64.99.    